val research conducted in the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, New Zealand and South Africa, this book remaps the intellectual geographies of Britain and its empire. In doing so, it provides a new context for writing the history of ideas and offers a critical analysis of the connections that helped fashion the global world of universities today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEducation, HigherxHistoryx19th centuryxEurope. 0aEducation, HigherxHistoryx19th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aEducation, HigherxHistoryx20th centuryxEurope. 0aEducation, HigherxHistoryx20th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aEducation, HigherzEuropexHistoryy19th century. 0aEducation, HigherzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aEducation, HigherzGreat BritainxColoniesxHistory. 0aEducation, HigherzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aEducation, HigherzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducation, HigherzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aUniversities and collegeszGreat BritainxColoniesxHistory. 0aUniversities and collegeszGreat BritainxHistory. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aAustralia.  aBritain.  aCanada.  aNetworks.  aNew Zealand.  aPractice.  aSociability.  aSouth Africa.  aSpace.  aempire.  aglobalisation.  aknowledge.  auniversities.1 aPietsch, Tamson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499176040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784991760423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784991760/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles